[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bangkok explosion in pictures

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A huge bomb blast hit the Thai capital, Bangkok, on Monday evening. At least 20 people were killed and more than 120 injured.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The bomb hit the Erawan shrine, a Hindu holy site which is also popular with Thai Buddhists and tourists.
These are some of the latest images from the scene, as police search for evidence.
The blast hit at 19:00 local time on (11:00 GMT) on Monday evening, when the shrine was busy with visitors
